thread.title: Eerie photos from the Apollo lunar missions
thread.title_full: Eerie photos from the Apollo lunar missions - seattlepi.com

author: JAKE ELLISON, SEATTLEPI.COM STAFF
title: Eerie photos from the Apollo lunar missions
text:
You've seen all the most famous shots of the cold-war-era missions that took men first into space and then to the moon and its surface, but there's a lot of images in a new aggregated archive of the Apollo missions you probably haven't seen that strike us as "eerie."
Meaning: They capture the strangeness of the moon, the cold desolation of space and that moonscape, the only celestial body besides Earth that humans have stepped on. These images, just snapshots really, capture the strangeness of space and inversely the mystery that Earth alone (so far as we know) harbors life.
Check out all the photos on the Project Apollo Archive Flickr page and read about the curator of these images and much more, Kipp Teague, on these pages ... here and here .
